<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1553,2010]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,536]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1553,1578]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Description.</emphasis>
Male (
<figureCitation box="[433,504,1553,1578]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1492,1514]" captionTargetBox="[156,1425,206,1465]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,193,1471]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Dorsal habitus of Batraxis species. A. B. pilosa. B. B. spinosas. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258824/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[489,504,1554,1578]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Body reddish-brown, pubescent, length 
<quantity box="[1016,1124,1553,1578]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="2.05">2.05 mm</quantity>
. Head rectangular, slightly longer than wide, HL 
<quantity box="[402,505,1590,1614]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.48">0.48 mm</quantity>
, HW 
<quantity box="[573,676,1590,1614]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.42">0.42 mm</quantity>
, vertex moderately convex, with median pit in middle of small but distinct vertexal foveae; antennal tubercles raised; frons with complete subantennal transverse sulcus, lacking vertexal sulcus; each eye composed of about 
<number box="[663,691,1662,1686]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="20.0">20</number>
facets; antennae thick, antennomere III–VII as long as wide, VIII slightly transverse, IX distinctly transverse, X transverse, XI largest, widest near base, then obliquely narrowing toward apex; median gular carina narrow, with two clearly separated small nude gular foveae. Pronotum slightly wider than long, PL 
<quantity box="[383,486,1770,1794]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.40 mm</quantity>
; PW 
<quantity box="[548,651,1769,1794]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.45">0.45 mm</quantity>
, with distinct median antebasal fovea and complete basal impression, with pair of lateral antebasal foveae and outer pair of basolateral foveae. Elytra wider than long, EL 
<quantity box="[1279,1381,1805,1830]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.53">0.53 mm</quantity>
, EW 
<quantity box="[151,253,1842,1866]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.74">0.74 mm</quantity>
, with two pairs of distinct foveae at base. Protrochanters strongly protuberant at ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[1343,1411,1841,1866]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1978,2000]" captionTargetBox="[194,1378,204,1949]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[188,1382,193,1961]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Diagnostic features of male Batraxis species. (A – D. Protibia. E. Mesotibia. F. Mesofemur. G – L. Protrochanter). A, G. B. bicolor. B, F, H. B. tibialis. C, I. B. pilosa. D, E, J. B. spinosas. K. B. hainanensis. L. B. minor. Scale line: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258827/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<date box="[1396,1411,1841,1866]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<number box="[1396,1411,1841,1866]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="5.0">5</number>
</date>
</figureCitation>
I); protibiae with small tooth preapically (
<figureCitation box="[588,655,1877,1902]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1978,2000]" captionTargetBox="[194,1378,204,1949]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[188,1382,193,1961]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Diagnostic features of male Batraxis species. (A – D. Protibia. E. Mesotibia. F. Mesofemur. G – L. Protrochanter). A, G. B. bicolor. B, F, H. B. tibialis. C, I. B. pilosa. D, E, J. B. spinosas. K. B. hainanensis. L. B. minor. Scale line: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258827/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[641,655,1877,1902]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Abdomen wider than long, AL 
<quantity box="[1051,1154,1877,1902]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.64">0.64 mm</quantity>
, AW 
<quantity box="[1218,1320,1878,1902]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.199999999999999" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.72">0.72 mm</quantity>
, distinctly narrowed at base; tergite IV (first visible tergite) with broad, abrupt basal sulcus; discal carinae elongate, widely separated, extending to two-thirds of tergal length, width between discal carinae 
<quantity box="[1102,1206,1950,1974]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.38">0.38 mm</quantity>
at apices; marginal carinae extending to apical two-thirds of tergal length. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[942,1013,1985,2010]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,210,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,193,1846]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Aedeagi of Batraxis species. (A, D. in dorsal view. B, E. in lateral view. C, F. in ventral view). A – C. B. pilosa. D – F. B. spinosas. Scale line: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258829/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[1000,1013,1986,2010]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
A–C) 
<quantity box="[1089,1194,1986,2010]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.39">0.39 mm</quantity>
in length, relatively elongate, parameres slightly exceeding apex of median lobe, rounded apically, each with one preapical seta; endophallus with series of symmetric sclerites and small, weakly sclerotized median sclerite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,536]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Female. Very similar to male in general appearance; protrochanters and tibiae lacking spur; each eye composed of about 
<number box="[251,279,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="10.0">10</number>
facets. Measurements: BL 
<quantity box="[586,689,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.02" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="2.02">2.02 mm</quantity>
; HL 
<quantity box="[745,848,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="0.48">0.48 mm</quantity>
; HW 
<quantity box="[913,1016,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="0.43">0.43 mm</quantity>
; PL 
<quantity box="[1068,1171,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.40 mm</quantity>
; PW 
<quantity box="[1231,1334,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="0.45">0.45 mm</quantity>
; EL 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="0.52">0.52 mm</quantity>
; EW 
<quantity box="[260,363,295,320]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="0.76">0.76 mm</quantity>
; AL 
<quantity box="[418,521,295,320]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="0.62">0.62 mm</quantity>
; AW 
<quantity box="[584,687,296,320]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="0.73">0.73 mm</quantity>
; width between discal carinae of tergite IV 
<quantity box="[1175,1275,296,320]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="0.38">0.38 mm</quantity>
at apices.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,536]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,434,332,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
The unique combination of characters of 
<taxonomicName box="[918,1090,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Batraxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis box="[918,1090,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Batraxis pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
quickly separates this species from all other congeners from Hainan, i.e. the long pubescence of the body, the presence of a median pit between the vertexal foveae in both sexes, the strongly raised antennal tubercles, and the aedeagus with apically rounded parameres slightly exceeding the median lobe, and with complicated and symmetric endophallus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
